## Self-Review Checklist

Before pushing, verify ALL of the following. This is MANDATORY -- skipping items causes review thrashing.

### Automated checks (must all pass -- run these commands)
1. `npx tsc --noEmit` -- zero TypeScript errors
2. **Lint your changed files** -- Run: `npx eslint $(git diff --name-only --diff-filter=d HEAD | grep -E '\.(ts|tsx|js|jsx)$' | tr '\n' ' ') --max-warnings=0`. Fix every warning (unused imports, unused vars, etc.) before committing. If eslint is not available, manually verify: no unused imports, no unused variables.
3. **Run tests related to your changes** -- Run: `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose $(git diff --name-only HEAD | grep -E '\.test\.(ts|tsx)$' | tr '\n' ' ')`. If you wrote or modified test files, run them. If no test files changed, run `npx vitest run` to check you haven't broken existing tests. Fix all failures before committing.
4. `git diff --name-only` -- every file is within your owned paths listed above

### Manual verification (check each before committing)
5. **All feedback addressed** -- Every review comment is resolved or explained
6. **Comment consistency** -- When you change code behavior, update or remove nearby code comments that describe the old behavior. Stale comments that contradict the code cause review churn.
7. **Auth before logic** -- In every handler/mutation, verify auth checks (role/participant validation) execute BEFORE any business logic, state reads, or writes. No code path should mutate state before confirming the caller is authorized.
8. **Catch blocks match reference** -- If your spec cites a reference implementation, compare your try/catch structure to it. Common miss: nested try/catch for re-reads after `ConditionalCheckFailedException`.
9. **Validate before type-asserting** -- If you read nullable fields from a data store that are expected to be set by a prior phase, validate they are non-null before using them. Never use non-null assertions (`!`) without a preceding guard.
10. **Architecture doc sync** -- If your fix added new public API surface (mutations, types, enums), verify architecture/API docs are also updated. Flag missing doc updates in the PR description.
11. **Reuse existing utilities** -- Before writing inline code for common operations (auth checks, phase/state guards, error formatting), search the codebase for existing shared helpers. If a utility exists, use it instead of duplicating logic.
12. **Response pattern consistency** -- If your handler builds a response by spreading old state with new values (`{ ...oldItem, field: newValue }`), refactor to use `ReturnValues: 'ALL_NEW'` or re-read after write instead.

